parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to inadequate restraint during an accident, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle breaks or fails to latch
allowing the occupant to move freely during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shoulder belt can cause inadequate restraint of the upper body during an accident, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The shoulder belt fails to restrain the upper body
allowing contact with the steering wheel or other objects
cracked or broken shoulder belt guide loops.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate seat belt restraint can lead to injuries or fatalities during an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to lock up during impact
resulting in injuries to the driver or occupant
the driver's head hits the seat belt molding during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to a potential loss of control and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, it can cause engine damage, oil and coolant leaks, and even fires.

The failure of the engine head gasket can cause oil and coolant to mix, leading to engine damage, leaks, and potentially fires. It can also cause the engine to shut down, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The malfunction of the engine can cause a loss of acceleration, making it difficult to maintain speed, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle is in reverse or when the brakes are applied.
symptoms: the vehicle accelerates suddenly while applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to not stop within a reasonable distance, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor
excessive premature wear to brake pads
vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in serious injury or death.
The transmission slipping or lurching can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Transmission hesitates or lurches when shifting into gear
especially when cold or after a period of inactivity
vehicle takes longer than usual to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Vehicle Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause vehicle fires, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle catches on fire under the dashboard or in the engine compartment
often originating from the wiring harness or electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to vehicle stalling or failure to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle stalling or failure to start.
